	  <div class='row'>
		<div class='column'>
			<p>I feel I grew the most in my persistence skills in the Scratch Project. In fact, it is uncanny how similar 
			these projects are. I start out great, but later I find myself struggling immensely just to fulfill the 
			requirements. Before the Scratch project, I would've given up by now. But now, I still haven't given up, 
			somehow. I've used my persistence skills to be able to actually finish the project without missing any 
			requirements. Regardless, my growth in these skills is evidenced by the fact that, knowing the deadlines, I 
			used my time management skills to experiment with code during my freetime, rather than during proper 
			worktime.In the beginning of the school year, I spent most of my time on asethetics, and less on actually 
			completing the goal. 
			</p>
